1
00:00:13,166 --> 00:00:14,666
[FREE] The great
War of Unification

2
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:16,958
began in U.E. 481.

3
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:21,291
This fierce conflict dragged on
for fourteen years.

4
00:00:22,708 --> 00:00:26,500
During that time, each nation
produced Fairy Soldiers.

5
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:28,250
Over three hundred in total.

6
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:32,416
[gunfire]

7
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,000
[roaring]

8
00:00:35,208 --> 00:00:38,250
[FREE] To do that,
Fairy imaginals were hunted.

9
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:42,666
[roaring]

10
00:00:43,791 --> 00:00:46,041
And hunted.
And hunted.

11
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:48,625
Until, there were practically
none left.

12
00:00:48,708 --> 00:00:50,333
[roaring]

13
00:00:50,416 --> 00:00:53,166
We turned these creatures into
instruments of war and murder.

14
00:00:54,958 --> 00:00:56,625
We fought.

15
00:00:56,708 --> 00:00:58,750
[grunting]

16
00:01:03,583 --> 00:01:06,166
[roaring]

17
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:08,250
-[FREE] And fought.
-[BEEVEE scoffs]

18
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:10,291
-[gunfire]
-[FREE] And fought.

19
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:13,708
[roaring]

20
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:17,625
Until finally...

21
00:01:20,416 --> 00:01:22,583
[roars]

22
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:26,208
We were nearly gone.

23
00:01:26,291 --> 00:01:29,166
As confirmed by
Unified Zesskia,

24
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:32,083
the number of Fairy Soldiers
that survived the war...

25
00:01:32,166 --> 00:01:33,583
[heavy thud]

26
00:01:33,666 --> 00:01:35,416
...was seventeen.

27
00:01:37,458 --> 00:01:39,083
[wind whistling]

28
00:01:46,958 --> 00:01:49,791
[WOLF] We killed each other
like mindless fools.

29
00:01:49,875 --> 00:01:52,791
And ended up slaughtering
the innocent in the process.

30
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:55,958
[panting]

31
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:06,500
[inhales sharply]

32
00:02:12,208 --> 00:02:13,625
[breathes shakily]

33
00:02:16,958 --> 00:02:19,083
-[OLD MAN] Is that you, Wolfran?
-[WOLF gasps]

34
00:02:19,166 --> 00:02:21,583
[OLD MAN] I can’t believe it!
You’re alive!

35
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:22,916
Thank goodness.

36
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,708
The fighting in these parts
was so fierce,

37
00:02:24,791 --> 00:02:26,125
I thought you’d been killed.

38
00:02:26,208 --> 00:02:27,791
[WOLF]
What about my wife and daughter?

39
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:29,833
Are they safe?

40
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:31,375
No, I’m afraid not.

41
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:32,541
[gasps]

42
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:36,333
[breathing shakily]

43
00:02:37,458 --> 00:02:39,666
[crying]

44
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,541
This isn’t real.

45
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,791
[WOLF]
Was it retribution?

46
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:49,875
Punishment for my actions?

47
00:02:49,958 --> 00:02:52,583
♪

48
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,166
[birds chirping]

49
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:02,958
[liquid bubbling]

50
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:05,250
[leather straps creaking]

51
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:14,416
[WOLF]
Beevee Liscar. Sir.

52
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,041
[BEEVEE huffs]

53
00:03:17,583 --> 00:03:18,750
[BEEVEE]
It’s ugly.

54
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,583
Absolutely repulsive.

55
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:22,291
I’ll never get over them.

56
00:03:22,375 --> 00:03:25,458
Their very existence
represents the peak of hubris.

57
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:27,916
And yet they happen to be
the tools of our trade.

58
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,541
You surprise me.

59
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:31,583
Are you a merchant, Wolfran?

60
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:32,708
Or a warrior?

61
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:35,375
Maybe nothing more than a pawn.

62
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:40,166
Colonel, it’s time.

63
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:41,625
[BEEVEE chuckles]

64
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:51,750
[WOLF]
I’m none of those things.

65
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:54,750
♪

66
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,708
-[MAN A] Nothing over here.
-[MAN B] Same for me.

67
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,583
[FREE]
Plenty of room.

68
00:04:12,666 --> 00:04:15,083
Enough to manufacture
artificial fairies.

69
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:17,166
Must’ve cleared out
before we arrived.

70
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:19,250
-Damn.
-They moved fast.

71
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:20,666
The place is deserted.

72
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,791
He’s quick on his feet.

73
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:24,500
That’s Wolfran.

74
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:09,000
[panting]

75
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,041
-[gasps]
-[FREE] Axel.

76
00:06:18,125 --> 00:06:19,708
Why are you running from me?

77
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:21,500
Hey. Wait!

78
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:24,666
That information I gave you
was completely legit, right?

79
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:27,166
About the transaction,
and the factory.

80
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:28,708
-Sure was.
-[AXEL groans]

81
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:30,250
[groaning]

82
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,375
Arcame must be pretty upset.

83
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:34,083
And real interested
in getting their hands

84
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:35,708
on whoever leaked the info.

85
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:38,250
Please. Like they’d ever
find out that it was me.

86
00:06:41,166 --> 00:06:43,666
I’m looking for Wolfran.
Ya know him?

87
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:45,291
Heard his name
come up before.

88
00:06:45,375 --> 00:06:47,833
See what you can find out.
It pays.

89
00:06:47,916 --> 00:06:49,916
My docket’s a little full, man!

90
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,791
I’ve still got
Arcame work to do!

91
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:55,333
Get lost.

92
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:57,750
Both you guys
are slave-drivers, I swear.

93
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:00,333
[MARLYA] So this time
we’re acting under the direction

94
00:07:00,416 --> 00:07:01,750
of the Ministry of Fairies?

95
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,708
[FREE]
By order of Director Nein.

96
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:06,250
Well, more of a request
than a command.

97
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:08,583
It’s not that unusual
for Dorothea and the Ministry

98
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:09,958
to cooperate on assignments.

99
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:12,041
[MARLYA]
Interesting.

100
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:15,458
Here we are.

101
00:07:15,541 --> 00:07:18,833
Vice-Minister Marco Bellwood
awaits you inside.

102
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:21,291
-Thank you.
-[CHIMA whimpers]

103
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:23,375
[knocking on door]

104
00:07:23,458 --> 00:07:25,375
[MARCO]
The door’s open.

105
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:29,000
The agents from Dorathea
have arrived.

106
00:07:29,083 --> 00:07:30,791
You wished to speak
with us, Vice-Minister?

107
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:33,000
[CHIMA whines]

108
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:35,333
Yes. Please both
of you have a seat.

109
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:41,291
Oh! That’s an extremely rare
species you brought along.

110
00:07:41,375 --> 00:07:43,750
-[CHIMA sniffing]
-[MARCO] A Czeschka maticarna!

111
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:46,416
A Cheska-what now?

112
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,875
[laughing]
Oh! Forgive me.

113
00:07:49,958 --> 00:07:52,333
It’s the animal’s
scientific name.

114
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:54,291
[FREE]
It’s a mouthful.

115
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:56,166
[CHIMA sighs contentedly]

116
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:58,041
[MARLYA chuckles]

117
00:07:58,125 --> 00:08:00,458
[MARLYA]
How about “Chima” for short?

118
00:08:00,541 --> 00:08:01,583
To business.

119
00:08:01,666 --> 00:08:03,375
I imagine you have some idea

120
00:08:03,458 --> 00:08:06,000
why I requested a meeting
with agents of Dorothea.

121
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:08,458
My guess is the Black Fairy Tome
has been found.

122
00:08:08,541 --> 00:08:11,250
Yes. We have a report
from a fairy scholar

123
00:08:11,333 --> 00:08:13,500
that the text has been
successfully recovered.

124
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:15,750
It seems pretty popular.

125
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,916
Just curious.

126
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,875
Are there other fairy tomes
with different colors

127
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,000
associated with them?

128
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:25,083
There certainly are.

129
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:27,500
The term "Fairy Tome" refers

130
00:08:27,583 --> 00:08:30,541
to the "Certified Text"
published by Alan Bach.

131
00:08:30,625 --> 00:08:31,916
The earliest to be written

132
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,750
was the original work
by Hel S. Bellwood,

133
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:36,583
the first fairy scholar.

134
00:08:36,666 --> 00:08:39,583
Next came Jay B. Mercer’s
"Blue Fairy Tome,"

135
00:08:39,666 --> 00:08:42,791
followed by Timothy Connor’s
"Red Tome."

136
00:08:42,875 --> 00:08:45,583
Colen Thor’s
"White Tome" was after that.

137
00:08:45,666 --> 00:08:50,125
And finally, Crucia Albastora
with his "Black Fairy Tome."

138
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,541
It was Bach who compiled
these different texts

139
00:08:52,625 --> 00:08:54,250
into one collected book.

140
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:56,166
That was nearly
200 years ago.

141
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:58,458
Wait, did you name a Bellwood?

142
00:08:58,541 --> 00:09:01,166
I happen to be a descendant
of the original author

143
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:02,666
and first fairy scholar.

144
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,041
[inhales sharply]
That’s very impressive, sir.

145
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:08,416
So he wrote the first text
and there are six in total.

146
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:12,166
Which are Blue, Red, White,
then, lastly, Black.

147
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:15,333
And together, they comprise
the Fairy Tome?

148
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:17,916
[MARCO] You’re close,
however, there’s one issue.

149
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,333
The pages of the Black Tome

150
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:21,625
are not contained
within the collected works.

151
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:23,375
But we know they exist.

152
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:25,833
Since the table of contents
references the text.

153
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:28,083
That’s precisely right.

154
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:30,125
We have some idea
what the tome covers

155
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:32,250
thanks to the few pages
we’ve gathered.

156
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:34,083
We know the writings
are on the subject

157
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:37,666
of some sort of phenomenon
known as “fairy possession.”

158
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:40,458
In any case,
the Ministry’s purpose

159
00:09:40,541 --> 00:09:41,916
is to oversee the management

160
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,791
of any fairy-related
knowledge and technology.

161
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,541
Securing the Black Fairy Tome

162
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:49,041
is a matter of grave
concern for us.

163
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:51,750
Only you’re not alone.

164
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:56,291
So, where are we supposed
to find this book?

165
00:09:56,375 --> 00:09:58,750
Go to Isharat.

166
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:01,500
Once you arrive
in the City of Towers,

167
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:04,583
a scholar named Cain Distarol
should help you.

168
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,791
And of course this matter
should remain confidential.

169
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:10,208
To the grave, sir.

170
00:10:14,833 --> 00:10:17,458
[engine chugging]

171
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:43,541
[FREE gasps]

172
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:45,958
[MARLYA grunts]
Where--

173
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:47,333
What was that all about?

174
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:48,458
[FREE]
Shh!

175
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,083
It is her.

176
00:10:51,166 --> 00:10:52,958
What is Sweetie doing here?

177
00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:54,666
Is she your...

178
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:56,833
-you know, sweetheart?
-You’re nuts!

179
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:58,958
-Me and her?
-[SWEETIE] Well, well.

180
00:10:59,041 --> 00:11:00,625
-Hello, Free!
-[FREE grumbles]

181
00:11:02,458 --> 00:11:04,458
[groans]
Perfect.

182
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:07,583
Of all people,
that Dorathea guy’s here.

183
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:08,791
Not only him.

184
00:11:08,875 --> 00:11:11,208
I also gotta deal
with Bitter Sweet?

185
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:13,750
She’s the famed leopardess
of Gui Carlin.

186
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,166
Just my luck.

187
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,875
[FREE] What the hell
are you doing here?

188
00:11:17,958 --> 00:11:19,416
[SWEETIE]
I could ask you the same.

189
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:22,458
I heard from the organization
you screwed up majorly.

190
00:11:22,541 --> 00:11:24,250
-So how is life on the run?
-[MARLYA gasps]

191
00:11:25,958 --> 00:11:28,375
-Sorry. Who’s this?
-Free!

192
00:11:28,458 --> 00:11:30,166
A bit young for you, isn’t she?

193
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,833
-That does it!
-Um, actually...

194
00:11:31,916 --> 00:11:33,291
[FREE] So, you wanna
know her story?

195
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:35,833
This woman works
alongside the damn mafia!

196
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:38,333
Not like she’d ever come clean
and admit to it though!

197
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:39,583
Mafia?

198
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:40,833
[scoffs]

199
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:42,916
I’m a legitimate
business woman.

200
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,000
As well as a world traveler.

201
00:11:45,083 --> 00:11:48,708
Young lady,
you may call me Bitter.

202
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,458
[AXEL]
“It’s a simple job, Axel.”

203
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:52,000
[scoffs] Yeah right.

204
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:54,041
Stealing the Black Fairy Tome
from a senile old man

205
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:56,166
would be a cinch
if those three hadn’t shown up.

206
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:59,750
Gah! You gotta wonder
if it’s even worth the trouble.

207
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,125
[groans]

208
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:03,458
Maybe I ought to just quit
Arcame.

209
00:12:03,541 --> 00:12:05,291
But, if I don’t
go through with this,

210
00:12:05,375 --> 00:12:06,833
they may bump me off.

211
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:08,583
[groans]

212
00:12:08,666 --> 00:12:10,583
[grunting]

213
00:12:10,666 --> 00:12:12,541
Time to pull off a miracle.

214
00:12:15,125 --> 00:12:16,583
-[FREE] Whoa, hold on!
-[SWEETIE gasps]

215
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,708
[sultry giggle]
Come, now.

216
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:22,250
If you were so desperate
to have me,

217
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:23,708
all you had to do was ask.

218
00:12:23,791 --> 00:12:25,625
-Just be gentle. [giggles]
-I changed my mind!

219
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:26,916
Knock on the door, please!

220
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,416
[SWEETIE]
What? And interrupt this moment?

221
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:29,541
Who are you?

222
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:30,875
No loitering allowed here.

223
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:32,750
-Uh, well...
-[SWEETIE giggles]

224
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:35,041
Is the doctor home?

225
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:38,041
Cain, it appears we have
several visitors today.

226
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:40,833
Well, if it isn’t Bitter Sweet!

227
00:12:40,916 --> 00:12:42,541
How long has it been?

228
00:12:42,625 --> 00:12:44,875
Apologies for
receiving you like this.

229
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:47,625
You know it doesn’t make
any difference to me.

230
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:49,208
I trust you’re in good health.

231
00:12:49,291 --> 00:12:51,250
Not too bad for my age.

232
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:53,500
I hope the same
can be said for you.

233
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:54,791
As for you two...

234
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:57,000
-[FREE chuckles nervously]
-[MARLYA] Hmm!

235
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:58,375
It’s been a while.

236
00:12:58,458 --> 00:13:00,541
I’m quite glad
you stopped by as well.

237
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:03,125
Of course.
It’s been far too long.

238
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:05,541
Right.
Good to see you again.

239
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:10,541
[bell tolling]

240
00:13:10,625 --> 00:13:13,125
[DAMIEN]
Ah, is it that hour already?

241
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:16,208
The evening bell of Timoon
serves many purposes.

242
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:19,875
The men use it as a signal for
when to begin their revelries.

243
00:13:19,958 --> 00:13:21,791
Surely not just the men.

244
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:25,083
-[leaves rustle]
-[AXEL grunts]

245
00:13:27,083 --> 00:13:29,666
[grunting]

246
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:31,291
[panting]
Like they say,

247
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:32,833
if you ever want
to make it to the top,

248
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:34,708
you gotta take some risks.
[chuckles]

249
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:37,041
[groaning]

250
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,583
Doctor.

251
00:13:39,666 --> 00:13:42,166
This 499 Rabica is exquisite.

252
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:43,708
You know your wine.

253
00:13:43,791 --> 00:13:46,916
Well, my father got our family
started in the business.

254
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,750
So Damien from
what I understand,

255
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,416
you’ve known Cain
for quite some time

256
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,416
and share a close bond.

257
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,875
My entire life.

258
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:55,541
The man has known me
since I was just an infant.

259
00:13:55,625 --> 00:13:57,708
-[softly] And what about us?
-[DAMIEN] Hmm.

260
00:13:57,791 --> 00:13:59,458
[softly] The Black Fairy Tome
is in my room.

261
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:01,791
Guaranteed safe and secured.

262
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:06,041
I heard a rumor.

263
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:07,291
Is it true you’ve recently

264
00:14:07,375 --> 00:14:09,500
gotten your hands
on a rarity, doctor?

265
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:11,041
-[CAIN] Huh?
-[MARLYA gasps]

266
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:14,000
[laughs softly] What exceptional
hearing you have.

267
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:16,625
Many things are exceptional
about her.

268
00:14:16,708 --> 00:14:19,250
Well, alright,
I’ll show you as a favor.

269
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:20,958
Uh. Damien, please.

270
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:22,500
[DAMIEN]
Right away.

271
00:14:26,041 --> 00:14:27,583
Well it is small.

272
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:30,958
But imaginals that resemble
humans are highly valuable.

273
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:33,500
Really? Is that because
there’s never been a case

274
00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:35,375
where a primordial
possessed a human?

275
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:38,375
So, you do know
owning that is illegal.

276
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:40,375
If you’re caught,
you could end up arrested.

277
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:42,875
And naturally, I’ll inform
the proper authorities

278
00:14:42,958 --> 00:14:44,458
in the near future.

279
00:14:44,541 --> 00:14:46,958
Surely, Unified Zesskia
isn’t oppressive to the point

280
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:48,375
it would obstruct
the research

281
00:14:48,458 --> 00:14:50,750
of an insignificant fairy
scholar like myself.

282
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:53,458
Who are you calling
insignificant, you genius?

283
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:54,958
No, but really,

284
00:14:55,041 --> 00:14:56,958
the find I was actually
talking about earlier was...

285
00:14:57,041 --> 00:14:58,250
[chirping]

286
00:14:58,333 --> 00:14:59,958
-[chirping]
-[MARLYA gasps]

287
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:02,333
-How cute!
-[screeches loudly]

288
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:04,291
[FREE]
Oh! Or not.

289
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:06,500
-[BOTH gasp]
-A fairy?

290
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,916
-[chirping]
-I know this trick!

291
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,375
-There’s a thief!
-[chirping]

292
00:15:10,458 --> 00:15:12,333
[gasps] The tome!

293
00:15:12,416 --> 00:15:13,833
-[FREE gasps]
-[objects clatter]

294
00:15:13,916 --> 00:15:15,541
I’ll follow him!

295
00:15:19,708 --> 00:15:21,375
[sighs] It’s safe.

296
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,041
[BOTH grunt]

297
00:15:23,125 --> 00:15:25,333
-[DAMIEN grunts] No!
-[AXEL laughs]

298
00:15:27,541 --> 00:15:28,916
-I see you! Crap!
-[chirping]

299
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,125
Not you! Get outta here!

300
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:31,708
We’ve been had.

301
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:34,458
The Black Fairy Tome is gone!

302
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:47,208
[footsteps running]

303
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:51,916
I see him!
That way!

304
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,333
Good eye, kid!

305
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:55,166
[FREE]
Hey! Wait!

306
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:56,791
Told you. Ha!

307
00:15:56,875 --> 00:15:58,541
Like a walk in the park!
[groans]

308
00:15:58,625 --> 00:16:00,291
Crap, Bitter Sweet!

309
00:16:00,375 --> 00:16:01,625
-That's just great!
-[chirping]

310
00:16:01,708 --> 00:16:03,750
No, Pillywiggin! Don’t attack!

311
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:04,958
[chirping]

312
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:07,208
What an adorable fairy you have!

313
00:16:09,875 --> 00:16:10,833
[groans]

314
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:13,083
That useless, little, no-good...

315
00:16:13,166 --> 00:16:14,750
Nobody asked you to help!

316
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,250
Just like I thought,

317
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:18,708
Sweetie was after
the same thing we were.

318
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:20,750
She probably already
found the thief by now.

319
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:22,041
[gasps] There he is!

320
00:16:22,125 --> 00:16:23,750
[gasping]

321
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,541
Where you going, Axel?

322
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,916
[AXEL panting]
Move it!

323
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:30,541
I don’t think so.

324
00:16:30,625 --> 00:16:32,041
Get outta my way!

325
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:35,583
[grunting]

326
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,041
[chuckles]

327
00:16:38,125 --> 00:16:39,833
[PATRONS gasp]

328
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:42,291
Son of a! [yells]

329
00:16:42,375 --> 00:16:44,958
Now where’d they run off to?

330
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:47,333
[PATRONS chattering]

331
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:49,666
[glass shattering]

332
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,250
[yelling]

333
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,458
[SWEETIE] I don’t dislike
persistent men.

334
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:55,625
But still...

335
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:56,791
[scoffs]

336
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,500
There!

337
00:17:02,666 --> 00:17:04,791
Doesn’t she ever quit?

338
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,583
[AXEL grunting]

339
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,333
[AXEL screams]

340
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:15,416
[chuckles]

341
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:18,333
[BOTH grunt]

342
00:17:18,416 --> 00:17:20,208
-[footsteps departing]
-[SWEETIE groans]

343
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,541
[whistle blowing]

344
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:27,833
Security Forces.

345
00:17:27,916 --> 00:17:30,125
Marlya, keep pursuing
both of them.

346
00:17:30,208 --> 00:17:32,041
Yes, sir!

347
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:33,750
What’s with all the commotion?

348
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,208
Special assignment.

349
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:38,833
[CAPTAIN]
You’re with Dorothea?

350
00:17:38,916 --> 00:17:40,458
How can we be of service?

351
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:42,416
We’re chasing after a suspect.

352
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,333
-Join in.
-Sir!

353
00:17:44,416 --> 00:17:46,666
[AXEL panting]

354
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:48,375
-Coming through!
-[WOMAN yelps]

355
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,166
-[whistles blowing]
-[AXEL groaning]

356
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,958
Fine!
If you want it so badly!

357
00:17:58,458 --> 00:17:59,625
[growls softly]

358
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:01,333
[panting]

359
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,416
[panting]

360
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:08,375
-[CAPTAIN] Halt!
-[whistles blowing]

361
00:18:08,458 --> 00:18:11,375
Look at all the chaos
our little lure has caused.

362
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:14,791
Cain even assisted
in setting it up.

363
00:18:14,875 --> 00:18:18,333
This diminishes my faith
in humanity immensely.

364
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:22,208
Looks like you won’t be
needed tonight, Veronica.

365
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:23,333
Seems that way.

366
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:24,958
[panting]

367
00:18:25,041 --> 00:18:26,208
[VERONICA]
The girl.

368
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:30,208
I think she might be
fairy possessed.

369
00:18:30,291 --> 00:18:31,875
You’re serious?

370
00:18:31,958 --> 00:18:35,541
Marlya, what has
happened to you?

371
00:18:35,625 --> 00:18:37,250
[AXEL panting]

372
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,083
[DAMIEN]
The Black Fairy Tome.

373
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:40,625
Fairy possession.

374
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:42,875
Arcame. Gui Carlin.

375
00:18:42,958 --> 00:18:44,166
Dorothea.

376
00:18:44,250 --> 00:18:45,375
[AXEL grunts]

377
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:46,666
[panting]

378
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,291
[DAMIEN] So many pieces
on the board.

379
00:18:50,958 --> 00:18:53,250
See? I can pull it off
when I really try.

380
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:54,958
-[SWEETIE] Pull what off?
-[AXEL gasps]

381
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:57,541
[SWEETIE]
I appreciate tenacity in a man,

382
00:18:57,625 --> 00:19:00,000
but not to the point
where he can’t accept defeat.

383
00:19:00,083 --> 00:19:02,208
You mean you haven’t
broken a sweat?

384
00:19:02,291 --> 00:19:03,708
How is that even possible?

385
00:19:03,791 --> 00:19:05,000
Are you even human?

386
00:19:05,083 --> 00:19:08,458
I can be a monster,
if you force me to.

387
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:10,583
Whoa, not forcing you.

388
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:13,333
I mean couldn’t even
if I tried to!

389
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:15,291
You have something I want.

390
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:16,666
Hand it over.

391
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:20,333
Fine. You win.

392
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:23,208
Or maybe not.

393
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,333
[FREE]
Evening.

394
00:19:25,416 --> 00:19:27,458
Both of you.

395
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,666
So you finally caught up.

396
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,208
Seems you lost
your little friend.

397
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:32,791
[FREE]
Guess so.

398
00:19:32,875 --> 00:19:34,916
[SWEETIE] You were infiltrating
Gui Carlin, weren’t you?

399
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,416
[FREE scoffs] I don’t know
what you’re talking about.

400
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,333
What happened
to the Fairy Soldier

401
00:19:39,416 --> 00:19:41,666
who was ready to fight
for Ledrad to the very end?

402
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:44,833
Tell me, do you like
working for Dorothea,

403
00:19:44,916 --> 00:19:48,375
and being made to kiss Unified
Zesskia’s ass on a daily basis?

404
00:19:48,458 --> 00:19:49,708
You’ve got a way with words.

405
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:51,541
Sorry if I offended,

406
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:54,250
but the thought of you
being a dog for government is,

407
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:56,166
honestly, a little sad.

408
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:58,666
The war ended a long time ago.

409
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:01,583
So you’re telling me you took
the job just to survive?

410
00:20:01,666 --> 00:20:04,291
It was the only way
you could live?

411
00:20:04,375 --> 00:20:05,875
What a joke.

412
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:09,583
[FREE] I don’t expect you
to understand my reasons.

413
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,041
-[AXEL grunts]
-[SWEETIE gasps]

414
00:20:11,125 --> 00:20:12,125
[AXEL panting]

415
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:13,708
-[gunshot]
-[AXEL groans]

416
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,625
-[AXEL groaning]
-You were warned.

417
00:20:17,708 --> 00:20:20,416
I don’t like men
who don’t know when to quit.

418
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:22,500
Yeah, but you didn’t
have to shoot him.

419
00:20:22,583 --> 00:20:23,958
[scoffs] He’s alive, isn’t he?

420
00:20:24,041 --> 00:20:26,083
[AXEL]
Sorry. Should’ve listened.

421
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:28,708
But I’ve also got a job.

422
00:20:28,791 --> 00:20:31,500
And I knew it carried
certain risks.

423
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:32,458
Here, catch.

424
00:20:32,541 --> 00:20:34,541
[AXEL laughs]

425
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:36,291
[AXEL]
It’s between you two.

426
00:20:36,375 --> 00:20:39,208
♪

427
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:46,125
[BOTH grunting]

428
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:50,583
[groans]

429
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:04,083
[gun clicks]

430
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:07,166
You’d shoot me like Axel?

431
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:08,833
If you just turn
around and leave,

432
00:21:08,916 --> 00:21:09,958
maybe I’ll let you live.

433
00:21:10,041 --> 00:21:11,541
-[gunshot]
-[bullet ricocheting]

434
00:21:14,708 --> 00:21:16,083
[MARLYA]
Don’t move!

435
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:17,958
I’d rather not
have to shoot you.

436
00:21:20,458 --> 00:21:22,208
But if you force me, I will.

437
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:24,958
What a well-disciplined
young lady you are.

438
00:21:25,041 --> 00:21:26,583
I hate that.

439
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:28,541
[energy surging]

440
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:30,708
[roaring]

441
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,416
[FREE gasps]
She has a fairy?

442
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,750
-[MARLYA gasps]
-[gunfire]

443
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:37,625
[whooshing]

444
00:21:39,375 --> 00:21:40,791
[MARLYA exclaiming]

445
00:21:40,875 --> 00:21:42,625
Marlya! Hang on.

446
00:21:42,708 --> 00:21:44,250
Explain yourself.

447
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:46,000
What the hell did you do?

448
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:49,458
♪

449
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:50,750
[giggles]

450
00:23:24,875 --> 00:23:27,458
[footsteps approaching]

451
00:23:30,375 --> 00:23:32,458
Wait, aren’t you...?

452
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,416
[PATTY]
So what did you have in mind?

453
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:43,125
-[DIESE] If I break the law...
-[MARLYA] You can’t outlast me!

454
00:23:43,208 --> 00:23:45,333
[JONATHAN] I have a suspicion
you’ll wind up being considered

455
00:23:45,416 --> 00:23:47,500
-one of my finest masterpieces.
-[FREE] Just who is this bitch?

456
00:23:47,583 --> 00:23:48,458
[JONATHAN] Lady.

